topic.title: Abstract

body.p: The Ethernet Subsystem processes Ethernet frames. It holds 10GE, 25GE, 50GE, 100GE, 200GE and 400GE PHYs (PCS and FEC) up to an aggregate bandwidth of 600 Gbps. The ENET has several configurable functions to enable different OTN mapping by the MAPOTN Subsystem: BMP, GMP, GFP and IMP. It supports up to 60 flexible rate clients ranging from 10 Gbps, 40 Gbps and Nx25 Gbps up to 600 Gbps through the usage of FlexE. FlexE can be terminated, partially terminated (aware) or pass transparently (unaware) through the ENET Subsystem. Each client can be processed by the ENET through a CBR or MAC path connected to a central packet buffer. The ENET supports extraction/insertion of PTP, SyncE, and LLDP frames to/from the CPU Subsystem. Finally, it provides FlexE management overhead extraction and insertion ports.
